column6: I think the world's climate is changing
column7: I'm worried about the effects of climate change on my community
column8: I think it's too late to do anything about climate change
column9: I know about the history of flooding in my community
column10: I know what the government and local authority are doing to help my community to cope with climate change
column11: I understand the difference between climate change mitigation and climate change adaptation
column12: I think technology is the most important tool we have to help us to adapt to climate change
column13: I think interactive maps are a useful tool for talking about and demonstrating the effects of climate change
column14: Games are a good way to help us to imagine the effects of climate change
column15: Imagining what our lives will be like in the future is a good way to discuss adaptation to climate change
column16: I think that changing my own behaviour can help to limit the effects of climate change
